In Ghesite beliefs, the clouds are considered incorporeal spirits that exist solely as messengers. The winds are messengers as well, but are considered much stronger - as unlike clouds, the wind can be felt by humans - and are believed to have traits and characters of their own, as well as a unique role within the world. The West Wind, for example, comes down from the mountains and is considered cold and biting, yet reasoned, due to the fact that it is so predictable.

It's worth noting that the bloody age of Hakai had actually brought us something prized and desired! What's it, you might ask? WMDs? No. Poisons? Think again! Pulse lasers? Leave that box already!
At the times of violent free-for-all, medical technologies were crucial to keep everyone ready to fight, yet they've found a more honorable, peaceful application. As of 3020, cancer, Alzheimer's disease and heart attacks are pretty much unheard of, and surgery has become more efficient and less intrusive, with recovery time minimized to mere weeks. Gender confirmation surgeries had reached such a perfect point that it's practically impossible to discriminate transgender people from the rest.
